    "extras": [
      "May to September is the sweet spot for combining Almaty city walks with Charyn and Kolsai without dealing with snowbound roads or Astana's brutal winter wind.",
      "Carry some cash in tenge for park booths, rural transfers and guesthouses because card acceptance drops sharply once you leave Almaty and Astana.",
      "For Charyn and Kolsai, pre-arrange a bed in Charyn camp or Saty village before leaving Almaty because same-day walk-ins are unreliable on summer weekends.",
      "Talgo berths and Air Astana fares jump fast around school holidays, so book the Almaty-Astana and Astana-Turkestan legs several days ahead.",
      "Yandex Go works well in Almaty and Astana, but around Charyn, Saty and Turkestan you should rely on hotel-arranged drivers, shared taxis and offline maps.",
      "If you only have one week, skip Turkestan and focus on Almaty, Charyn Canyon, Kolsai Lakes and one overnight in Astana."
    ],
